description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Senior Immunisation Nurse / Team Coordinator within the outer London immunisation team within CNWL. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you caring, compassionate and committed to providing the best service possible for young people?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CNWL provides school aged vaccinations across Hillingdon, Brent and Ealing and several inner London Boroughs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, self-motivated, flexible and reliable registered nurse with previous experience working within an immunisation role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a demanding post which will involve assisting with the coordination of a team of nurses to provide the national immunisation programme within schools and clinics. You must possess good leadership qualities and be able to liaise with other multi-disciplinary health professionals and other bodies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Variable start and finish times will be expected between 08.00am and 17.00pm and you will need to be a car driver with use of a car and be able to drive to schools within Brent, Ealing and Hillingdon on a daily basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Be efficient and work under the direction of the immunisation team leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Be able to use own initiative and demonstrate good leadership qualities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Be self-motivated, with the ability to work well under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Have excellent written, verbal and interpersonal skills and a polite and courteous manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Maintain a professional attitude at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Demonstrate an up to date knowledge of the current UK childhood immunisation schedule, as well as knowledge to assess immunisation queries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The immunisation team work closely with other services and key stakeholders such as (but not exclusive to); school nursing teams, child health department, GPs, Public Health England and commissioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your commitment we will make sure you receive the support and development you need to prepare yourself for future challenges. We provide good supervision and a first class learning experience in all aspects of community immunisation. We also make it easy for you to access continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CNWL is recognised locally, nationally and internationally for providing high quality, innovative healthcare. We aim to employ only the best people, and our experts are frequently called upon to contribute to national health strategy and policy, and many models of our care have been adapted for use in other countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
